expectancy of life and the ageing of the HIV positive population, tumors are now 
one of the major cause of death, and among them hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) 
has become a growing concern in these patients. Considering the potential 
anti-tumoral effects of HIV protease inhibitors, we decided to evaluate the 
anti-tumoral activity of Amprenavir on liver carcinoma and to evaluate its 
