The burden of dengue in Nicaragua has been steadily rising during the last three 
decades; however, there have been few efforts to quantify the burden (measured 
in disability-adjusted life years [DALYs]) and cost to society. Using primary 
data from the Nicaraguan Ministry of Health (MINSA), the total cost and burden 
