cost was estimated to be US$13.5 million/year (range: US$5.1-27.6 million). This 
analysis can help improve allocation of dengue control resources in Nicaragua 
and the region. As one of the most comprehensive analyses of its type to date in 
Nicaragua and Latin America, this study can serve as a model to determine the 
burden and cost of dengue.

